This individual adjustment is performed manually, with the peeling machine 10 still, by an operator, only during the assembly of the machine, or in the event of maintenance. The individual adjustment is performed as follows:
1) the cover 29 is removed;
2) the screws 40 are unscrewed;
3) the hub 39 is removed until abutment, in order to disengage the gear 35 from the toothed wheel 36;
4) the calibrated screw 21 is rotated to the right or left, until the desired setting is obtained;
5) the hub 39, the screws 40 and the cover 29 are re-assembled.
